<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Transport Select Committee – Inquiry into Strategic Road Network</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 85.05pt"><span style="color:#096d4c; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 85.05pt"><span style="color:#096d4c; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Highways Term Maintenance Association (HTMA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">) (SRN 013)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I am responding on behalf of the Highways Term Maintenance Association (HTMA) to your invitation to comment on your call for evidence on the strategic road network.</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The HTMA is the trade </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">organisation which represents service providers who currently maintain around 80% of the highway network within the United Kingdom.  The Association aims to deliver high quality maintenance and asset management services, whilst seeking to drive positive ch</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ange within the industry, for the communities within which we work.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Association welcomes the acknowledgement in the government’s command paper, Action for Roads, of the importance of road maintenance to the economic and social growth of the United Kin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">gdom.  It is for that reason that we would stress the importance of striking an appropriate balance between investment in new infrastructure and maintenance of the existing asset.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Association wishes to comment on Issue 4 of your call for evidence, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">“Ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">w can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road network? What impact will new technology have?”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Strategic road users place a high value on the road network and their expectation is that it will provide them with safe travel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, reliability of journey time and a minimum of disruption to their journeys. The presence of roadworks on the network, whether caused by maintenance or improvement schemes, is a frequent cause of driver complaints as well as a considerable cost to the econ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">omy. It is important therefore that a maintenance strategy based on an asset management approach is adopted. This will require commitment to a long term programme of investment, with a steady predictable profile, early visibility of the funding stream and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">early engagement with the maintenance delivery sector.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A maintenance strategy as described above will help to reduce unplanned maintenance interventions on the network and lead to better managed maintenance activity. It is important that this maintenance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">activity is planned within the overall management of the network as road users do not distinguish between different types of activity on the network whether it be maintenance, improvement or utility driven.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">New technology supporting Building Information M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">anagement (BIM) will have a significant impact in providing a readily available and easily understood knowledge resource that will improve asset management decision making throughout the life of the scheme. This will be linked to data and information colle</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ction technology improvements.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Further developments in technology will improve real time journey information for road users which is vital in improving safety, reducing travel costs and improving user perceptions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 2pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#096d4c; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>